Electro-Federation Canada Senior Data Analyst


Electro-Federation Canada (EFC) is a national, not-for-profit association representing the dynamic electrical and automation industries, contributing to Canada’s net-zero future, intelligent buildings, smart infrastructure, and Industry 4.0. EFC’s 220 member companies consist of manufacturers, distributors, manufacturers’ representatives and field service organizations. EFC members contribute over $10B to the Canadian economy and employ over 43,000 workers in more than 1,400 facilities across the country. EFC is recognized as one of Canada’s ‘Great Places to Work’ for three consecutive years.


We are currently seeking a full-time Senior Data Analyst to make a difference and assist companies in Canada’s electrical and automation industry with data analytics to deliver insights to support critical decision making.


Electro-Federation Canada (EFC) has a robust statistics department that provides market share data to its members in several product and market verticals.


Under the supervision of the President & CEO, the duties and responsibilities of the Senior Data Analyst include, but are not limited to, the following:


Work with EFC business section verticals and the distribution community to understand the market drivers of their businesses;
Work closely with leadership teams to create data strategies that support data modeling;
Develop and implement databases and data collection systems;
Acquire data from existing, primary and secondary sources and maintain data systems;
Utilize existing market data to identify, analyze and interpret trends or patterns in complex data sets;
Analyze data using statistical techniques and provide reports;
Prepare reports and presentations to communicate business insights for forecasting market trends to members; and
Help support data requirements for EFC’s research and the industry’s Pathfinder benchmarking report.


The successful candidate will possess the following qualifications:


Your ability to ask questions and uncover relationships between market drivers and business segments will help you craft the data system required to deliver valuable insights.


Bachelor’s Degree in Business, Computer Science, Mathematics or a related field;
Minimum of three (3) to five (5) years of relevant work experience;
Highly competent using Excel, SQL, R/Python, Power BI or Tableau;
Exceptional written and verbal communication and presentation skills;
Ability to present complex information in a simplified way to tell a story, backed by data to communicate insights to a variety of audiences;
Self starter with a curious and analytical mindset;
Ability to work independently and to work with cross-functional teams;
Ability to organize, prioritize and follow through on important projects; and
Strong attention to detail.

Why you'll love working at EFC:

Competitive employment package;
Flexible working schedule;
Dynamic team and positive work culture;
Open-concept, state-of-the-art office environment;
Onsite gym;
Summer hours; and
Complimentary on-site parking.

The position offers a competitive employment package and compensation commensurate with experience in a friendly and collaborative work environment.


EFC welcomes and encourages applications from people with disabilities. Accommodations are available on request for candidates taking part in all aspects of the recruitment and selection process.


For more information, check us out online at https://www.electrofed.com

